¬∃ k\*<y\*> = k\*<x\*>
.SEME

Create a new template, not based on any current template.

.TP
Extend a template
.SEM(t, ...) ⊢ \fBTemplate\fR source:E\*<+\*> \fB{\fR a:(A / O / X)* \fB}\fR ↓ < (t, ..., s, ...); k\*<x\*> → k\*<x\*> >

(t, ...) ⊢ source ↓ S = < (s, ...); k\*<s\*> → e\*<s\*>, ... >,

∀ aa ∈ a, (∃ k\*<s\*> : k\*<x\*> = k\*<s\*>) : e\*<s\*> ⊢ aa ↓ k\*<x\*> e\*<x\*>,

∀ aa ∈ a, (¬∃ k\*<s\*> : k\*<x\*> = k\*<s\*>) : aa ↓ k\*<x\*> e\*<x\*>,

